merged = "/samurlab1/RawData/Romain/Projet/Hemm/Data/merged_/myeloid.R"
load(merged)

stage_df = read.csv("/samurlab1/RawData/Romain/Projet/Hemm/Data/stage.csv", header=FALSE)
merged@meta.data["tissue"] = unlist(lapply(merged@meta.data$orig.ident, function(x)
{return(str_split(x, "_")[[1]][[2]])})
)

merged@meta.data["patient"] = unlist(lapply(merged@meta.data$orig.ident, function(x)
{return(str_split(x, "_")[[1]][[3]])})
)
merged@meta.data["stage"] = unlist(lapply(merged@meta.data$orig.ident,
                                          function(x){
                                            ifelse(strsplit(x, "_")[[1]][[3]] %in% stage_df$V1,
                                                   stage_df[stage_df$V1 == strsplit(x, "_")[[1]][[3]],]$V2,
                                                   "Relapse")}))
merged@meta.data["inter"] = apply(merged@meta.data, MARGIN=1, FUN=function(x)
{return(paste(x["patient"], x["tissue"], x["stage"] , sep="_"))})

Scaled bar graphs for figure 1C

monocytes_bm = as.matrix(monocytes$tissue == "BM")
bm_barcodes_mat = monocytes_bm[monocytes_bm %in% TRUE,]
length(bm_barcodes_mat)
## [1] 60914
bm_barcodes = names(bm_barcodes_mat)

monocytes_bm = subset(monocytes, cells = bm_barcodes)
  # DimPlot(monocytes_bm)

metadata = monocytes_bm@meta.data[monocytes_bm$tissue == "BM",]


# Creating a summary data frame
summary_data <- metadata %>%
  group_by(patient, metadata$active.ident) %>%
  summarize(count = n(), .groups = 'drop') %>%
  group_by(patient) %>%
  mutate(proportion = count / sum(count), .groups = 'drop')


# Create the bar plot using ggplot2
x = ggplot(summary_data, aes(x = patient, y = proportion, fill = `metadata$active.ident`)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "fill") +  # 'position = "fill"' makes it a scaled bar plot
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format()) +  # Convert y-axis to percentage
  labs(title = "Bonemarrow clusters of CD11b+ monocytes",
       x = "Condition",
       y = "Proportion",
       fill = "")+
       scale_fill_manual(values = colors )  +
  theme_minimal()

order = c("546342","451572","330568","367841","540483","361445","551452","543036","517450","548291","479545","329771","447073","408420","519606","234868")
x$data$patient <- factor(x$data$patient, levels=order)
x
